(216, 'Received from Rahul - 2026-03-13: [https://www.linkedin.com/in/jagdeep-singh-805b55124?utm_source=share&utm_campaign=share_via&utm_content=profile&utm_medium=android_app](https://www.linkedin.com/in/jagdeep-singh-805b55124?utm_source=share&utm_campaign=share_via&utm_content=profile&utm_medium=android_app) Groww director/business head of broking starting up ---'),
(217, 'Post-Meeting Investor Debrief: The investors expressed skepticism after the meeting. Concerns raised included: - Lack of clear moat despite claims of simple, superior design - Questions about why Xiaomi (known for despeccing products) hasn''t implemented similar design improvements - Uncertainty about learnings from previous startup failure/wind-down - Doubts about founder''s ability to scale in a difficult category The investors agreed to pass on the opportunity. This is all the malls, Phoenix, PurchaseLegal, Nexus, It''s all of the chains, right? McDonald''s, Subway, KFC, a lot of independent types are for $1,000. We''ll start with one. So that was my bread and butter for the longest time. Then in 2021, we decided we wanted to do something else. We no longer wanted to be an app, but we wanted to continue driving to fall to stores. So we came up with what is today the only affiliate program for offline stores, which is like seamless, clean, neat, etc. I ran that for three years until 2024. We raised a lot of money for that business. We were backed by all of the amazing folks, founders of Swiggy, Razorpay, Mama Earth, and so on. I was building a company with my fiancee at the time. We parted ways. And I decided I don''t know, I wanted to pursue that opportunity. We were lucky enough to get an acqui-hire from Razorpay, but we turned that down because it was like one next invested capital for a three-year lock-in. But instead, we rolled up a trust and all of my investors got equity i...'),
