(221, '**Background and Role at MPL:**: - Hired during COVID (2019) as Rachit''s replacement in design leadership - Initially hired as AVP of design but needed grooming for the role - Later became head of design after an intermediate hire was let go - Successfully aligned the design team with objective business KPIs - Demonstrated steady leadership during turbulent times, including a 60% team reduction **Key Strengths:** - Meticulous and calm under pressure - Resilient and reliable during challenging periods - Excellent people leader (7-8/10 rating) - Strong at lateral and downward management - Objective in difficult decisions, not letting personal relationships affect judgment - Considered among the top 5 design managers Rachit has worked with **Areas for Development:** - Not strong at upward management - Inverted priority hierarchy: Team > Design > Product > Company (should be reversed) - Rated 5-6/10 as a business leader - Unclear if he would have the foresight to preemptively identify business challenges - Receptive to feedback but had limited progress in business orientation **Recommendations:** - [ ] Consider advising Ketan to find a co-founder who is stronger on business acumen - [ ] Conduct additional reference checks to verify business capabilities - [ ] Assess whether Ketan''s business perspective has evolved since leaving MPL ---
RM Notes: 1. Hired Ketan to replace himself - during COVID | 2019 1. Rachit was going to start another initiative within MPL 1. 2-3 months in real...'),
